body:
To define a federated database instance store with Google Cloud, you can specify the
configuration parameters in JSON format. The configuration contains the
Google Cloud data store and maps it to virtual collections that you can query.

The JSON configuration for data in Google Cloud uses the
following fields:

```json
{
  "stores" : [
    {
      "name" : "<string>",
      "provider" : "<string>",
      "region" : "<string>",
      "bucket" : "<string>",
      "prefix": "<string>",
      "delimiter": "<string>"
    }
  ],
  "databases" : [
    {
      "name" : "<string>",
      "collections" : [
	{
	  "name" : "<string>",
	  "dataSources" : [
	    {
	      "storeName" : "<string>",
	      "path" : "<string>",
	      "defaultFormat" : "<string>",
	      "provenanceFieldName": "<string>",
	      "omitAttributes": <boolean>
	    }
	  ]
	}
      ],
      "maxWildcardCollections" : <integer>,
      "views" : [ 
	{
	  "name" : "<string>", 
	  "source" : "<string>", 
	  "pipeline" : "<string>" 
	}
      ] 
    }
  ]
}


```

The JSON configuration for Google Cloud contains
two top-level objects: [stores](adf-gcp-stores-reference) and
[databases](adf-gcp-databases-reference)
